Woodbury University is a small, creative institution located in the heart of one of the most exciting places in the world. Watch this to see what we’re all about.
Since 1884 Woodbury has been a leader in higher education.

Woodbury students get hands-on experience, real-world connections, and a top-tier education. Woodbury alumni have built thriving businesses, run magazines, established accounting and design firms, become notable fashion designers for film and television, won design competitions, built award-winning buildings, held public office, and led growing organizations.

Located in the San Fernando Valley, the Woodbury University campus lies adjacent to the Verdugo foothills near the Angeles National Forest. The school straddles the dividing line between Los Angeles and Burbank, providing students with the best of both cities ranging from world-class film and entertainment studios to the LA Fashion District to the region’s thriving creative and startup community.

Woodbury San Diego occupies a renovated warehouse in the Barrio Logan district. Sited between downtown and the naval shipyards, the campus is a center of cultural and architectural activity in a diverse neighborhood populated by families, artists, and community leaders. Faculty and students play an active role in shaping the future of the area through events, workshops, and outreach.

Located on the iconic Hollywood Boulevard Walk of Fame, the Woodbury University Hollywood gallery (WUHO) provides a welcoming space for multi-disciplinary, boundary-crossing collaboration and supports the study and practice of the design disciplines.

Woodbury School of Architecture will be hosting a portfolio workshop. The workshop will begin with a presentation that covers general portfolio design guidelines and best practices. Following the presentation, applicants will have an opportunity to present their portfolio to a faculty member for direct feedback. We look forward to working with you on your application materials.This workshop is for transfer undergraduate and graduate applicants only.
February 29, 2020 - Creative Workshops – College of Liberal Arts
Creative Workshops – College of Liberal Arts

High School juniors and seniors, here’s an opportunity to explore your creative potential. Learn about Woodbury University’s College of Liberal Arts and explore the range of creative programs that COLA has to offer. Take one of the following free hands-on workshops:
→ Explore Poetry, Prose, and Performance // Creative Writing
→ My Path to Success! // Personal Statement Writing
→ Policing and Mental Health // Public Safety Administration
→ Fun with Data Mining // Computer Science Data Analytics
Note that you must be a high school junior or senior to attend one of these workshops
Join us for the “MBA Experience” to learn more about our AACSB-accredited MBA program. At this event you will have an opportunity to:
Get an introduction to Woodbury University
Hear from the School of Business Dean, Dr. Joan Marques, and the Associate Dean and Director of the MBA program, Dr. Satinder Dhiman, who will talk about the program and the student experience
Participate in a Q&A with faculty and alumni
Application fee waivers will be provided to all attendees
Refreshments and snacks will be provided, and free parking is available on campus
April 4, 2020 - Architecture Portfolio Workshop - Basics for Beginners (San Diego)
Are you a high school or community college student that is ready to design portfolio for the first time?
Then this is the workshop to attend!
In this 2-hour workshop we will cover the following:
– Content: What type of work to include in a portfolio.
Why you should attend this workshop:
– To have an awesome portfolio to apply to a college/university.
– To have an awesome portfolio when applying for jobs.
Add to your skill set now! Sign-up for our workshop.
